concept.title: DIMBASELINE Command
concept.shortdesc: Creates stacked dimensions from the same baseline.

conbody.p: Create stacked linear, angular or ordinate dimensions from the same baseline as an existing dimension. The dimensions are based on the current dimension style and the dimension spacing is specified by the DIMDLI variable.

section.title: Methods to create baseline dimensions
section.p: There are two methods to begin creating baseline dimensions:

dlentry.dd: Begin creating baseline dimensions from the last linear, angular, or ordinate dimension by specifying a point for the next extension line.
For linear and angular dimensions, the first extension line of each baseline dimension coincides with the first extension line of the previous dimension.
Continue placing dimensions until you press Enter to end the command.
Begin creating a baseline dimension by selecting an existing linear, angular, or ordinate dimension then:
Specify a point for the next extension line.
For linear and angular dimensions, the first extension line is coincides with the extension line nearest to where you selected the existing dimension.
Continue placing dimensions until you press Enter to end the command.

section.title: Options within the DIMBASELINE command
section.p: After you begin creating a baseline dimension, the following option may be available:

dlentry.dd: Undo the last dimension and continue drawing from the previous dimension.
